      "text": "The Russian author Fyodor Dostoevsky (1821-1881) is reported to have said that somebody should not write a book until they have tried every­thing possible to prevent it being written. This is another in a long line of books that attempts to make a contribution to the leadership and man­agement of an organization that, because of information technology, is suddenly faced with rapid acceleration. Why have I not prevented this book being written?"
    },
